item.title: FTSE 100 Rises After Initial Losses as US Traders Return From Holiday
item.description: The FTSE 100 managed to edge higher, recovering from opening losses, with the focus already shifting to Thursday’s BOE rate decision.

item.title: German Two-Year Schatz Yield Unlikely to Rise Much from Current Levels
item.description: The two-year German Schatz yield is trading at around 3.15% after rising roughly 40 basis points this month, aligning with UniCredit Research’s target for the end of September and leaving limited room for further rise.

item.title: Metals Mixed Amid Uncertain Macro Sentiment
item.description: Base metals were mixed with gold a touch lower as the macroeconomic outlook remained uncertain, said Peak Trading Research.

item.title: Lanxess Slides on Profit Warning
item.description: Lanxess shares dropped sharply after it downgraded its year-end earnings expectations, with some analysts questioning the success of the chemical company’s M&A strategy.

item.title: Europe Aims to Cut China Risks, Not China Ties
item.description: The European Union is set to release an economic-security strategy aimed largely at reducing the risks in its trade relationship with Beijing.

item.title: Dollar Loses Upward Momentum After Fed Skips Rate Rises
item.description: The dollar was flat in Europe and MUFG Bank said the currency has lost upward momentum after the Fed skipped raising interest rates last week for the first time in more than a year.

item.title: Oil Shrugs Off China Rate Cuts
item.description: Oil prices were largely unchanged in Europe, showing little reaction to a rate cut from China’s central bank which was widely expected.

item.title: Alibaba Is Replacing Chairman and CEO Daniel Zhang
item.description: Alibaba is replacing top executive Daniel Zhang by naming company veteran and Brooklyn Nets owner Joe Tsai as the new chairman.

item.title: Stellantis, Foxconn Form Chip Venture
item.description: Stellantis and Foxconn are joining forces to create a new equally-owned business that will sell semiconductors to the automotive industry, particularly for EVs.

item.title: New Zealand Government to Probe Banking Competition
item.description: New Zealand authorities have announced an investigation into profitability and competition in its banking sector amid concerns that lenders have made large profits while customers are managing cost-of-living pressures.

item.title: Silicon Valley's Newest Unicorn Is a Mining Company
item.description: Bill Gates and other tech-industry investors are backing AI-powered startup KoBold Metals.

item.title: China Cuts Borrowing Rates Again in Bid to Juice Recovery
item.description: Economists say that more drastic measures may be needed, with debt and uncertainty continuing to weigh on consumers’ willingness to spend.

item.title: India's prime minister said ties between New Delhi and Washington are stronger and deeper than ever as India moves to secure what Modi sees as its rightful place on the world stage at a moment of geopolitical turmoil.
